quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,6,"Surely for those who have disbelieved, it is all the same whether you warn them or you warn them not: they would not believe."
  2,7,"Allah has set a seal on their hearts and on their hearing, and on their eyes there is a covering; and for them there lies a mighty punishment."
  2,8,"And among men there are some who say, "We believe in Allah and in the Last Day", Yet they are no believers."
  2,9,"They try to deceive Allah and those who believe, when they are deceiving none but their ownselves, and they are not aware."
  2,10,"In their hearts there is a malady, so Allah has made them grow in their malady; and for them there lies a grievous punishment, for they have been lying."
  2,11,"And when it is said to them, 'Do not spread disorder on the earth", they say, 'We are nothing but reformers.""
  2,12,"Beware, it is, in fact, they who spread disorder, but they are not aware."
  2,13,"And when it is said to them, 'Believe as people have believed," they say, "Shall we believe as fools believe?" Beware, it is, in fact, they who are the fools, but they do not know."
  2,14,"And when they meet those who believe, they say, "We have entered Faith;" but when they are alone with their Satans, they say, 'Indeed, we are with you; we were only mocking.""
  2,15,"It is Allah who mocks them, and lets them go on. wandering blindly in their rebellion."
  2,16,"These are the people who have bought error at the price of guidance; so their trade has brought no gain, nor have they found guidance."